## Code Snippet Props

When using CodeSnippet components inside Code Groups, you have access to these props:

<ParameterField name="language" type="string" default="javascript">
Programming language for syntax highlighting. Supports all languages recognized by Shiki.
</ParameterField>

<ParameterField name="title" type="string">
Display title for the code block. Used as the tab label in Code Groups.
</ParameterField>

<ParameterField name="showLineNumbers" type="boolean" default="false">
Display line numbers on the left side of the code block.
</ParameterField>

<ParameterField name="highlight" type="string | number[]">
Highlight specific lines. Use comma-separated values or ranges (e.g., "2,5-7" or [2,5,6,7]).
</ParameterField>

<ParameterField name="wordWrap" type="boolean" default="false">
Enable word wrapping for long lines of code.
</ParameterField>

<ParameterField name="showInlineCopyButton" type="boolean" default="true">
Show individual copy button. Automatically disabled inside Code Groups.
</ParameterField>

## Best Practices

<Callout type="tip">
Place the most commonly used language or framework first in the Code Group. Users often default to the first tab.
</Callout>

<AccordionGroup>
  <Accordion title="Use descriptive tab labels">
  Provide clear `title` props that identify the language or framework:

  ```jsx
  <CodeSnippet language="javascript" title="Node.js with Express">
  ```

  This is clearer than just "JavaScript" when multiple JS frameworks are shown.
  </Accordion>
  <Accordion title="Keep code examples concise">
  Show only the relevant portions of code. Long examples reduce scannability:

  **Good:**
  ```jsx
  <CodeSnippet language="python" title="Authentication">
  {`headers = {'Authorization': f'Bearer {api_key}'}
  response = requests.get('/api/endpoint', headers=headers)`}
  </CodeSnippet>
  ```

  **Avoid:**
  Including full class definitions, imports, and boilerplate when only demonstrating authentication.
  </Accordion>
  <Accordion title="Maintain consistency across tabs">
  Ensure all code examples in a Code Group demonstrate the same concept or API call:

  **Good:** All tabs show how to make a GET request to `/api/users`

  **Avoid:** Mixing GET requests in one tab with POST requests in another
  </Accordion>
  <Accordion title="Use highlighting strategically">
  Highlight key lines that differ between implementations or emphasize important logic:

  ```jsx
  <CodeSnippet language="javascript" highlight="3-5">
  {`const config = {
    baseURL: 'https://api.example.com',
    timeout: 5000,
    headers: {
      'Authorization': `Bearer ${apiKey}`
    }
  };`}
  </CodeSnippet>
  ```
  </Accordion>
</AccordionGroup>

